name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
I hope you had the chance to see the “Salute to Utah” flyover from Ogden to St. George taking place this afternoon led by our F-35A team.

We are grateful for the hard work of our healthcare workers, first responders, other essential employees and all Utahns during this time. pic.twitter.com/gtwMh8PHBT

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We are watching data very closely as we enter the orange phase. If necessary, we will quickly transition back to red. Please exercise caution as we loosen restrictions this weekend. #utcovid19

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Doing the little things makes a difference. All of us working together to take precautions can make a big difference in slowing the spread of COVID-19.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Our press briefings will not be daily in the moderate phase. You can continue to expect updates from the State — and from @DrAngelaCDunn, but they will be less frequent.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
Previously closed businesses, including restaurants, bars, personal care facilities, salons, and gyms, can reopen when they exercise strict precautions. 

Dine-in options can resume, where eating establishments exercise strict precautions.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: What actually changes tonight at midnight? You can gather with small groups of family and friends (up to 20). But do not spend time with others if you are sick, even if your symptoms are very mild.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Wear a mask in public. Practice social distancing. Wash your hands as frequently as feasible. We are moving to orange, but now is not the time to relax.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Your efforts to follow orders and directives have given us time to build up supplies and capacity in our health care system. #utcovid19

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: At 12:01 tonight, Utah will transition from high risk to moderate risk — red to orange. There is reason for us all to be optimistic, as we implement our plan and exercise caution.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Register for an appointment at  http://dmv.utah.gov .

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Five DMV lobbies will be open again by appointment only starting tomorrow. The Hurricane lobby will also be open on a limited basis, starting tomorrow.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: A few quick observations - we are aware of crowing issues at our DMVs. For that reason. I have suspended enforcement on expiring vehicle registrations through May 15. This order is effective immediately.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: In the weeks since the purchase, we've determined that it's no longer prudent for the State to have this supply. I would like to thank the vendor, Meds in Motion, for accepting our request to refund the $800,000.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: The State of Utah has received a full refund on the  $800,000 purchase of chloroquine/hydroxychloroquine. We have determined that all involved acted proactively, preemptively and prudently during an emergency in an effort to save lives, and everyone acted in good faith. pic.twitter.com/4ZlGLdBiff

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: pic.twitter.com/gBeDmxJzfm

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Yes! Everyone should wear masks in public, and Utahns who don't have masks can get them free of charge here:  https://coronavirus.utah.gov/mask/

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: They haven't been required to close. Many businesses made closure decisions independently.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Masks are in production with the Utah Manufacturer's Association and @cotopaxi. Order fulfillment could take about three weeks.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
A Mask for Every Utahn will provide 2 million masks to Utahns, free of charge. 

Request a mask here:  https://coronavirus.utah.gov/mask/ 

Please request only one mask per person — and only request a mask if you do not already have one.  

#utcovid19 #masks #UtahMask

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We are beginning to enter a stabilization phase. We need you to take ALL precautions seriously. Moving forward into MODERATE RISK, or orange, and continuing our positive trends, is wholly dependent on you continuing to take precautions seriously.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Those who are vulnerable (or who interact with vulnerable individuals), should continue to exercise the most strict precautions.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
-Leave home for nonessential reasons. Try to do so infrequently. 
-Interact with groups of 20 or fewer people. 
-Dine-in at restaurants that exercise necessary and extreme precautions
-Visit personal care facilities, like gyms and salons, when they exercise extreme precautions.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
Starting Friday, May 1, you will be able to: 
- Gather with small groups of friends or family outside your immediate household, as long as everyone participating has been following distancing and hygiene guidelines. #utcovid19

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
Of course, continue practicing good hygiene. 
Wash hands with soap and water for at least 20 seconds as frequently you can, use hand sanitizer after interactions with people or objects, use masks, cover coughs or sneezes into the sleeve or elbow, don't touch your face.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
- You should still shop infrequently — make one large grocery shopping trip instead of many small ones.
- Carryout and delivery services at restaurants are still strongly encouraged,
- But dine-in services can resume IF restaurants meet strict distancing and hygiene requirements.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
- Interact with one another virtually. 
- Limit out-of-state travel, and quarantine for 14 days upon returning from higher-risk areas. 
- Continue social distancing at all times, including when you are outside, and do not let children play on playgrounds.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
- When it is not possible to stay 6 feet away from others, wear a face covering. 
- This could be a handmade mask, or a bandana. It does not need to be a medical grade mask. 
- Work from home, whenever possible.
- Stay home as much as possible.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
Our actions as individuals should not change much going from red to orange: 

- Take extreme precautions generally. 
- Stay 6 feet away from others when outside the home, unless not possible.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Not slipping back into “high risk” — depends upon YOU and your continued efforts to stay safe, to stay healthy and to stay strong by exercising great care in your social interactions, and exercising precautionary measures when you are in public.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Let me be exceedingly clear: Moving from HIGH RISK (red) to MODERATE RISK (orange) does NOT mean business as usual.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Utah is in a HIGH RISK, or RED phase. Today I am announcing, in coordination with @UtahDepOfHealth, that Utah will transition to MODERATE RISK, or ORANGE phase, on Friday, May 1. pic.twitter.com/RMvDuf4RDC

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We identify which level of risk our communities are facing by analyzing a data dashboard, which compares data on hospitalizations, hospital capacity, and testing, to name a few key metrics.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
- RED indicates a HIGH RISK, 
- ORANGE indicates MODERATE RISK, 
- YELLOW would show a LOW RISK, and 
- GREEN indicates what we might call our “NEW NORMAL RISK” for COVID-19, meaning, even in green, all of us need to exercise caution and care.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We are diligently following the Utah Leads Together plan. It is directed by medical science and data. It contains a color code — pic.twitter.com/nkwchndWmg

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Just as impressive as what we have been able to do as institutions is what you have done individually. You are adapting, you are even more self-reliant than we thought. And you are protecting each other.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We have procured over 5 million N95 or KN95 masks, over 4 million surgical gowns, and over half a million face shields. We are continuing to build up these supplies.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We've also been working to increase our medical capacity: We have created isolation and quarantine sites statewide, we have worked with our hospitals to offer a coordinated standard of crisis care.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We have built up a strong contact tracing capacity, with nearly 1200 health officials supporting that effort. They are supported by the Healthy Together app, which you can download from the Apple Store or Google Play.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: With the help of @UofUHealth and ARUP, we are putting in place large-scale prevalence and incidence studies to understand Utah's exposure to COVID-19, as well as focused antibody testing to deploy to healthcare, frontline workers, and critical infrastructure workers.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We have set up 62 different testing sites around the state, and three mobile test collection units that work with vulnerable populations around the state.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We have greatly increase our capacity to test and trace for COVID-19. We can currently conduct 6,000 tests per day, and we can do lab work for 9,000 tests per day.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: I'm grateful to the people of Utah for following instructions to #StaySafeStayHome. This has allowed us to build up capacity in our healthcare systems, and to stay within our hospital capacity.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: The dashboards I'm referring to are health data dashboards.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Participation is, and always will be completely voluntary. This is a resource for Utahns who feel comfortable using it.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: If you download Healthy Together AND you choose to share location data, you help share more accurate information with the public health worker reaching out to you as part of the process.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: 23,000 people downloaded the app in the first 36 hours it was available. Every person helps, since the app helps connect people with our teams at @UtahDepOfHealth.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We have seen good developments in antibody testing and hope to begin introducing it soon.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We're watching testing closely. We are regularly testing over 4000 Utahns every day and providing 56 test sites. Coming developments in antibody testing will introduce a whole new layer of testing.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Next week we will provide more information in our press briefings to help better acquaint ourselves with what life under MODERATE RISK, or Orange, will look like.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: There are at least six data-rich dashboards updated daily on hospitals, quarantine, active cases, state entry points, hospitalizations, and supplies & resources. Together, these give us a picture of where we are and our readiness to move from one risk rating to another.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: These health officials then notify the close contacts. We have over 200 people detailed to this effort.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Public health officials are doing case investigations, and notification of close contacts. This involves interviewing all newly identified positive cases, determining who they have been in contact with, determining which of those contacts are considered to be "close" contacts.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
- Statewide non-ICU bed utilization is currently at 5%
- There is demand to treat non-COVID-19 medical issues to ensure individuals are getting the medical help needed. This demand can be managed based on current hospital utilization

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
2) We look very closely at capacity data: 

- Our hospitalization numbers have been stable for the last two weeks. 
- Currently, the statewide ICU utilization is less than 17%
- Over the last two weeks, ICU utilization has hovered between 15% and 17%

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
The number of new hospitalizations has been declining since April 8, and using our most conservative estimation of the data, has declined by 18% over the last seven days.

We estimate that the transition rate of the virus is near 1 to 1.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
We are not being guided by fear or politics. We will base these decisions off crucial data points, including: 

1) Trends in new hospitalizations (this tells us how the virus is spreading and if it is hitting populations that require high levels of medical intervention).

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: I am still reviewing recommendations from the Public Health and Economic Emergency Commission to transition Utah to an Orange phase. Good trends in data show that we could make that transition as early as the end of next week. pic.twitter.com/AxrhSUD9OL

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
6. Cover coughs or sneezes into the sleeve or elbow,not hands

7. Clean high-touch surfaces (buttons, door handles, counters, etc.) regularly

8. Avoid touching your face

9. Refrain from hand shaking

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
Our Utah Leads Together plan includes four color-coded levels of risk. We are still in red, indicating a high risk. Each color places us all under specific responsibilities. 

You can read more about the color-coded guidelines here:  https://coronavirus-download.utah.gov/Health/Phased%20Health%20Guidelines%20V3.pdf … pic.twitter.com/PoZzt6yhal

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Thank you Utah teachers! https://twitter.com/UtahCoronavirus/status/1253730758524616705 …

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Yes! We provide ASL translations of our daily briefings.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
We have also pushed out funding through @utahsenate and @utahreps, and provided agricultural help in the form of alfalfa and grain to the San Juan Southern Paiute Nation. 

We have also provided PPE, as well as food donations and hygiene materials.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We are also working to support our tribes. This has included providing mobile testing to the Navajo Mountain and Monument Valley areas of the Navajo nation, pushing out Public Health Emergency Preparedness funding to tribal programs and the Urban Indian Center of Salt Lake.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Our Refugee Education and Training Center through @JobsUT has assisted 1,722 individuals in 62 languages since March 30. Refugee Services provides daily email updates to refugees, community leaders, and refugee service providers throughout the state.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We are currently translating critical public health information into 18 languages, with five more soon to come.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
The subcommittee will also include partners from government and business, leaders of faith-based organizations, and community advocates. 

The co-chairs will be Zee Min Xiao, who is on the Utah Multicultural Commission, and Byron Russell, co-chair of the Multicultural Commission.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: This included important guidance about prevention, stay-at-home guidelines, job and housing protections and employment assistance.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Additionally, under direction of @SpencerJCox , this group recently underwent the process of putting together an extensive survey which shows us that these communities were not receiving many of the state’s messages as best as they could be.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: This has been reinforced by recent data from the state Health Department showing a higher rate of infection for Hispanic and Pacific Islander communities, in particular.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
These are uncertain and trying times for all of us, and the State of Utah is resolved to support all Utahns through this crisis. 

We all understand the challenges faced within these communities, especially when language barriers exist.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Today I am announcing the formation of the Utah Multicultural Task Force Subcommittee, which will serve as part of Utah’s COVID-19 Community Task Force. #utcovid19

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
What does Healthy Together do? 
-It helps you track symptoms
-It connects you with COVID-19 testing
-It can help public health identify potential cases by providing additional information to enhance contact tracing efforts
#utcovid19 #togetherutah pic.twitter.com/H8QNCUlZqw

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: You can choose to share location and bluetooth data in the app if you want to. If you do, that data will only be available to public health, who will still call you to work through contact tracing and other advice, if you test positive for COVID-19.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
Apple store:  https://apple.co/354hUZK 
Google Play: https://bit.ly/2yABalr

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: You can download the Healthy Together beta app today to track symptoms, and connect easily with COVID-19 testing throughout the state. Location data gathered through this app will also help @UtahDepOfHealth identify where COVID-19 is spreading.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: I hope that you and your loved ones will begin to make use of this app, even in its beta form. Be a part of the solution to create better tools for identifying outbreaks so that we can be more targeted in our response moving forward.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Combining our robust testing and contact tracing with insights from the Healthy Together app is like giving us binoculars to begin to see the virus more clearly from a distance.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
Aggressive testing and tracing is one way of taking the blindfold off. 

It can help us see better where the virus may be active.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
By participating in Healthy Together, you can play an active and critical role in protecting the people close to you, and everyone in our community. 

Because the virus is invisible, it feels like we have been battling it awhile blindfolded.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
-Location data will automatically be deleted after 30 days. 
-Symptom data will be automatically de-identified after 30 days. 
-Healthy Together will comply with State requirements for data security and encryption.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
We care about the privacy and security of Utahns' data, which is why: 
- Use of the app is strictly opt-in and voluntary
-Users own their data and can delete their data at any time. 
-Only data that is required to combat COVID-19 will be shared with public health officials.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: It will also help experts at the @UtahDepOfHealth engage in contact tracing, so we can understand where the virus is spreading.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: The app will help you assess your symptoms and connect to the abundant testing resources we've worked so hard to expand.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
Today I am announcing a new tool for Utahns — the Healthy Together App. This mobile app will help you and your loved ones track symptoms, and connect easily with COVID-19 testing throughout the state.
 https://coronavirus.utah.gov/healthy-together-app/ …

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Re: Reactivating the economy, we have tried to find the right balance. Our decisions have been guided by data, and they will continue to be guided by data. #utcovid19

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet:
And you can also view the Utah Hospital Association's roadmap for resuming procedures here: 
 https://coronavirus-download.utah.gov/Health/UHA%20CMO%20Group%20-%20Utah%20Guidance%20for%20Urgent%20Time-Sensitive%20Surgery%20v5%20(002).pdf …

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: You can view the full, updated public health order here:  https://coronavirus-download.utah.gov/Health/state%20public%20health%20order.20.04.21.pdf …

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Yesterday we opened up some opportunities for elective surgeries. This is an incremental step. It will help the medical profession resume some procedures while continuing to preserve hospital beds, PPE, and medicines.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We are making significant headway in the battle against COVID-19 thanks to Utahns working together and following directions from @UtahDepOfHealth. I feel cautiously optimistic about the trends we are observing.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Today, @UtahDepOfHealth issued an updated public health order allowing medical providers to resume some elective procedures. #utcovid19 pic.twitter.com/yfN7s0TuLd

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: This afternoon I issued a proclamation calling @UtahSenate and @utahreps into a special session. #utpol pic.twitter.com/ipMmifXxDP

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We are tracking our testing and contagion rates. Right now, we are still in the red, urgent phase, of Utah's coordinated response. As we continue to #StaySafeStayHome, we can contain Utah's outbreak, and hopefully transition to the orange phase soon. #utcovid19 pic.twitter.com/Zkgf5fBJqk

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Staying focused on health is a crucial part of Utah's plan to get people back to work. These will be our guiding principles. #utcovid19 #TogetherUtah pic.twitter.com/M848IciFyn

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We will base the reactivation of Utah's economy on data. We can simultaneously address health issues and support our economy, as we employ strong testing and hygiene measures to make public spaces safer. pic.twitter.com/GyDEOVMbdI

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We're working to lift restrictions on our State Parks and we are also hopeful to reopen National Parks to Utahns.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: I'm hopeful that we can resume some in-house dining, and some elective surgeries by the first part of May. I'm also hopeful that we will be able to reopen gyms. All of this depends on continued adherence to the #StaySafeStayHome directive.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Utah's trends are positive, but now is not the time to pull back on our safety protocols.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Utah Leads Together 2.0 gives a pathway forward to stabilize. A lot will depend on what we do individually over the next few weeks. As we continue to slow spread over the coming weeks, we will be able to respond appropriately.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Utah's plan is the most comprehensive plan of any state in America. That plan is underway.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: As we plan to reactivate the economy and enter the stabilization phase, strong social distancing measures, and the wearing of masks, will help us return to normal activities while preserving health.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: The Utah Leads Together Plan has three phases — an urgent phase, a stabilization phase, and a recovery phase. Today, we announce Utah Leads Together 2.0, which contains more details on our plans to reactivate our economy.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Inspiring to see our state come together to fight COVID-19. Thank you to @joshjames and the team of people at @siliconslopes who came together to bring 8 million pieces of PPE to Utah. #TogetherUtah pic.twitter.com/pLofvIC9MT

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We are encouraged by the COVID-19 data we are seeing so far, and we are making plans for how and when we will lift some restrictions. But Utah is still in an urgent response phase, and we will be for some time. Continue to follow guidance to #StaySafeStayHome. #utcovid19

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Thank you also to parents and students for all you are doing to make sure education continues from home.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We're tremendously grateful to all our teachers and counselors who are working hard to teach and take care of their students from a distance. I'm grateful for the creativity and resilience of all who are involved.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: In consultation with the Utah State Board of Education, I have determined that we need to extend the soft closure of our public and charter schools through the remainder of the school year. #utcovid19

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: In-house dining at restaurants will be prohibited through the end of the month, but take out and delivery options are still available.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: Please wear homemade masks when you are in public places where you may encounter other people -- like grocery stores and other shops. This will help prevent the spread of disease. #utcovid19

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: I look forward to working with @utahsenate and @utahreps to make sure these funds go to those who need them most.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: I'm grateful for the opportunity to work with @NatlGovsAssoc and the @WhiteHouse to negotiate directly for Utah's needs. We worked directly with @stevenmnuchin1  to ensure that a large portion of response funding will be available to states through flexible block grants.

name: Gov. Gary Herbert
tweet: We are tracking COVID-19 data closely in Utah and we are encouraged by the trends we see so far. We will continue making data-driven decisions to #FlattenTheCurve and save lives.
